dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Maryport, drift, sheet 22
dc_description_s: Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England (Third Edition) Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 22 drift. Geological Survey of Great Britain. North Decimal Degree 54.816700. South Decimal Degree 54.6667. East Decimal Degree -3.3833. West Decimal Degree -3.8167. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of England (Third Edition). Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depths shown by contour intervals. "Original geological survey on the six-inch scale by R. Russell & T. V. Holmes. Published on one-inch Quarter Sheet 101 N.W. (Old series) in 1892. Carboniferous rocks revised by J.G. Goodchild, published 1895. Resurveyed by T. Eastwood (Senior Geologist), northern margin by L. H. Tonks (Geologist).".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1930.
